	<refsect1 id="glVertex.3G-parameters-v">
		<title>Parameters</title>
		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><parameter>v</parameter></term>
				<listitem>
					<simpara>
						Specifies a pointer to an array of two, three, or four elements. The elements of a two-element array are
						<parameter>x</parameter> and <parameter>y</parameter>; of a three-element array, <parameter>x</parameter>,
						<parameter>y</parameter>, and <parameter>z</parameter>; and of a four-element array,
						<parameter>x</parameter>, <parameter>y</parameter>, <parameter>z</parameter>, and <parameter>w</parameter>.
					</simpara>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="glVertex.3G-description">
		<title>Description</title>
		<para>
			<function moreinfo="refentry">glVertex</function> commands are used within <function
			moreinfo="refentry">glBegin</function>/<function moreinfo="refentry">glEnd</function> pairs to specify point, line, and
			polygon vertices. The current color, normal, and texture coordinates are associated with the vertex when <function
			moreinfo="refentry">glVertex</function> is called.
		</para>
		<para>
			When only <parameter>x</parameter> and <parameter>y</parameter> are specified, <parameter>z</parameter> defaults to 0
			and <parameter>w</parameter> defaults to 1. When <parameter>x</parameter>, <parameter>y</parameter>, and
			<parameter>z</parameter> are specified, <parameter>w</parameter> defaults to 1.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="glVertex.3G-notes">
		<title>Notes</title>
		<para>
			Invoking <function moreinfo="refentry">glVertex</function> outside of a <function
			moreinfo="refentry">glBegin</function>/<function moreinfo="refentry">glEnd</function> pair results in undefined
			behavior.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
